==English==

===Etymology===
[[panty]] + [[liner]]

===Noun===

{{en-noun}}
# A pad worn on the inner surface of women's underwear, up against the [[vulva]], during a shoulder-day of the menstrual period, designed to absorb small, spotty quantities of [[menstrual fluid]], in contrast to a [[tampon]] or [[sanitary napkin]], worn on heavy-flow days.

